00:18:57.030 --> 00:18:59.280 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that is
outside of our control.

00:18:59.280 --> 00:19:02.540 align:middle line:84%
But what we do is we can take
control of our lives again,

00:19:02.540 --> 00:19:04.550 align:middle line:84%
surrender, let go,
and we can get out

00:19:04.550 --> 00:19:06.060 align:middle line:90%
of that negative relationship.

00:19:06.060 --> 00:19:07.220 align:middle line:90%
We have to.

00:19:07.220 --> 00:19:11.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, that's our
responsibility to ourselves.

00:19:11.300 --> 00:19:14.660 align:middle line:84%
But most of us have been
brainwashed by society

00:19:14.660 --> 00:19:17.270 align:middle line:84%
to feel that we have
to stay with people

00:19:17.270 --> 00:19:20.960 align:middle line:84%
and heal them when
that is totally wrong.

00:19:20.960 --> 00:19:21.950 align:middle line:90%
>> But we can't.

00:19:21.950 --> 00:19:23.030 align:middle line:90%
We can't fix them.

00:19:23.030 --> 00:19:26.570 align:middle line:84%
We can maybe create a space for
another person to become better

00:19:26.570 --> 00:19:29.990 align:middle line:84%
or to heal themselves and we
cannot harm another person,

00:19:29.990 --> 00:19:32.570 align:middle line:84%
but you really can't fix
the other person, can you?

00:19:32.570 --> 00:19:34.370 align:middle line:84%
>> That's exactly
right, Georgia.

00:19:34.370 --> 00:19:37.100 align:middle line:84%
And in order to
take our power back,

00:19:37.100 --> 00:19:39.350 align:middle line:84%
we have to realize
that, and then

00:19:39.350 --> 00:19:42.290 align:middle line:84%
assume our responsibility
to our own selves

00:19:42.290 --> 00:19:44.630 align:middle line:84%
and take our focus
off the other person

00:19:44.630 --> 00:19:46.450 align:middle line:84%
and put our focus
on our own pain.

00:19:46.450 --> 00:19:47.430 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

